news.title: Hyderabad civic body introduces new system to assess property tax
news.para: The GHMC admitted that the existing property tax system was not citizen-friendly and said people were forced to visit zonal offices multiple times to get their assessments done.

news.title: Gurugram authorities seek to corroborate IIT-Delhi findings on Chintels Paradiso
news.para: The IIT Delhi in its report found that the collapsed building was "aging faster than expected" and had significant corrosion in its steel reinforcement.

news.title: Bombay HC orders Omkar Realtors to make Worli flat habitable within seven days
news.para: S P Kapadia and his wife had bought the 65th-floor apartment in ‘Worli 1973’ for Rs 23 crore in 2015 and completed payment in 2017. The HC also directed the builder to finish three private lifts for the flat in Tower A in three months.

news.title: In troubled waters, challenges get taller for Noida's realty sector
news.para: The UP-Rera website shows there are more than 70 projects across the state that have ended up at the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) for insolvency proceedings.

news.title: Give us refund at the earliest: NBCC Green View residents meet DC
news.para: At the meeting, they urged the DC to get an FIR registered against the developer for endangering their lives and demanded that the state-owned construction firm be blacklisted for all future projects in Gurgaon.

news.title: Bombay HC grants bail to Avantha Group's promoter in Yes Bank fraud case
news.para: The CBI had registered an offence against Thapar, Yes Bank founder Rana Kapoor and other accused under sections 120B (criminal conspiracy), 420 (cheating) of the Indian Penal Code (IPC) and sections 7, 11 and 12 of the Prevention of Corruption Act (PCA).

news.title: Sunteck Realty case: Sebi reduces penalties on five entities
news.para: ​The total penalty imposed on five entities is lower than the amount slapped on them through an order passed in December 2019.

news.title: Canada's housing market hints at cooldown as higher rates, inflation bite
news.para: The slowdown in major cities like Toronto and Vancouver and their surrounding areas appears to be gathering steam, driven by a confluence of factors.

news.title: Hibernia REIT recommends Brookfield unit's $1.20 billion takeover bid
news.para: Ireland's largest stock market-listed office landlord said the offer price, excluding a 3.4 euro cent dividend per Hibernia REIT share, represents a 35.6% premium to Thursday's 1.18 euro closing price.

news.title: Mumbai: Jailed DHFL director to be out of private hospital, must go to JJ
news.para: Earlier this week, the court sought an explanation from the private hospital on Wadhawan, earlier arrested in a corruption and cheating case involving Yes Bank.

news.title: IIT Delhi team questions quality of material used in Chintels Paradiso
news.para: Two women were killed after the dining room floor of a sixth-floor apartment of Tower D at Chintels Paradiso in Sector 109 came down on February 10, triggering the collapse of roofs and floors directly under it, till the first floor.

news.title: SC allows ex-Unitech promoter's wife to attend grandmother's funeral ceremony
news.para: A bench of justices D Y Chandrachud and M R Shah asked Preeti to submit her Dominican Republic passport or any other passport that she has to the investigating officer before being allowed out of the prison.

news.title: Aurangabad civic body awaits state government's instruction on property tax waiver
news.para: “The necessary policy decision is expected at the state-level and we have not received any communication so far,” the civic body told to the local unit of Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) in a letter issued on Thursday.

news.title: Agency gets one more month for final draft for New Noida
news.para: During a meeting on Thursday, the consultant was asked to study some of the best investment regions in the world and frame the master plan accordingly.

news.title: Hyderabad: No takers for Swagruha flats at auction
news.para: ​​The Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) has put 2,246 flats in Rajiv Swagruha Corporation’s Sahabhavana Township in Bandlaguda near Nagole and Jalaja Township in Khammam district for sale.
